				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Soloing in OOW New solo locations share them.<a name="63198"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 20 04 4:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><span class="Highlight">LVL 65+ soloing for this thread if possible.  Or named solo (doubt there is any).  Want to keep this thread open for sharing locations only really, hopefully add to guides or something.  IMO I have found enough locations to solo pre 65, in the PoP.  However any OOW soloing is welcome like I said for named/drops/quests/exp (better exp than previous locations not much point to solo in area's that have less exp than even Stalkers)  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /></span> 
<br />

<br />
I've tried soloing in OOW nothing I've found that is gonna be very feesable remember when you talk about soloing you don't want something you have to HOPE you don't die from that is less how good you are but that such and such snares you repeatedly or summons you.
<br />

<br />
Asking that those who post, post zone, general area (if you can easily), mob name, area you kite it in, and risks (I.E. Snare, DDstuns, DD, etc).
<br />

<br />
Hopefully this will give us some options.
<br />

<br />
(I know its my topic and this is off topic <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />) Found in PG if you have a necro friend there is an area that &quot;could&quot; be duo'ed gonna check on it tonight, approx 7%+ aa (at 66 with partner) I believe 1%+ regular exp at 66, will double check tonight.  Thank fully I've had a few necro's ask for duo's in the past even tho my chant damage (only 600 a tick atm =/ no crits either) but they like it for the run song, never have downtime literally (not that they have any in the first place i think :P)
<br />

<br />

<br />
===WoS, Murkgliders(sp), out from NC IZ to the right in the cave, Kited it out in the nice flat area in a wide pattern, snares but does not summon.===
<br />

<br />
I've solo'ed some of those &quot;gliders&quot; (will double check name later at work atm), but they tend to snare =/.  I found to avoid the snare, if you keep it at maximum chant range you are less likely to have it cast the snare on you, from my experiences... though I could be wrong.  Did this once, second time w/o buffs and im the sux bard only 3200 hp unbuffed, went and pulled at 75% or so, kept getting snared and got an add when wanderer showed up.  Waited for dots to wear off faded figured wasn't worth a death.  (I only scarifice myself to 10+ mobs :P).
<br />

<br />
I'm hoping to find some more mobs for us higher ups to solo but its looking to me most solo spots with good exp will be PoP exp. =/
<br />

<br />
Highlighted was edited in 4:48 9-20-04</span></td>
