				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing in OOW New solo locations share them.<a name="66470"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 6:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've kited the Murkgliders in Noble's Causeway somewhat.  Some of them cast a nasty poison dot but it's easy to keep ahead of it if you have Aria in your lineup.  They move slow enough that you don't need selo's even.  As you zone into NC from DS jump down in the pit area and you can easily single pull the murks to a large empty spot free of roamers with lots of room to kite right below the zoneline back to DS.  Exp here is about the same as PoV, the mobs have fewer hit points but cast that dot frequently.
<br />

<br />
The circular rooms in The Bloodfields is decent as mentioned, similar to HoH exp but the mobs have a LOT less hp than HoH mobs.  Problem is the casters mixed in who will dot and snare and dd you.  I cleared the first 2 rooms about 4 times before I reached a point where the snares were getting to me.. so I ran to a corner and Faded, medded up and pulled the casters single to a quite spot where I could take them out away from their friends.  There is a named High Priest that spawns right near the zone from DS who drops an Int caster face piece and +10 Attk Aug, Type 7.  The aug is his rare drop and he's a cleric who frequently Cheals himself, I just charm his buddies and send them at him while dotting him till he's dead, mana drain can speed this process up.
<br />

<br />
Most normal mobs in WoS summon, the girps, the chimeras and ferans and bazu etc.  The Murkgliders might be the only mobs that don't summon actually and they' hit pretty hard and can snare and dot you, not much hunting here solo but you could duo here with some clever strategy.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
