				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing in OOW New solo locations share them.<a name="66854"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 14 04 10:12 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>ZI in Ruined City of Dranik is very easy, 3 big golems, 1 noc, and a noc roamer that WILL add.  Selo's keeps you ahead, they bunch nicely and don't cast anything.  I've heard that trash do have a chance of dropping nice stuff, though the spawn rate means I have trouble stopping to loot as they're continually keeping up spawn rate.  It's something todo while waiting LFG.  Xp is good, but it's a long kite, these things have huge amounts of hps.  Only chance I've had to loot was as mob about to drop, head towards zo, hope it dies before having to zone, pop out,back in again.  Not personally seen anything as it's usually a pain todo, once again, partner really needed for this, if only a loot buddy.  Invis works for a fair bit of the zone in, so it's not a bad place to explore, though watch for wandering named.  There's a named murkglider that wanders around the bridge area that is a hard hitter, but the entrace is all good exploration, so move to a spot, and start kiting.
<br />
Bloodfields works in a few spots, not amazing xp, but given the choice between Rathe Mountains on betweenRaidTime or kiting for a bit of xp, this place will do.
<br />
Tried in Harbingers' Spire, but the mob speed and limited room makes this a bit tricky.  Will try again with new snare when I get chance and see how it works out for me.
<br />

<br />
Jyve AFK</span></td>
