				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing in OOW New solo locations share them.<a name="68569"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 31 04 10:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've found a nice solo location in RCoD.
<br />

<br />
On the map its a large room at the top to the right of the Slayer.
<br />

<br />
In the room there are 12 elite kyv, 2 stoneworkers and a Discord Fluctuation.
<br />

<br />
I like to aggro and kite the 4 kyv near the Fluctuation..
<br />
I use about 1/3 of the room to kite staying far enough from the other kyv and stoneworkers to not aggro.
<br />
If only kiting one kyv, when it nears death, it will have to be snared so it doesn't wander off and bring adds
<br />

<br />
Leave the stone workers alone... if its a baleful stoneworker it doesn't cast, however if you were to kill it, a transmuted stoneworker may replace it.
<br />

<br />
Transmuted stoneworkers are shaman and they do root <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
The elite kyv are lvl 68... I was getting 1% of lvl per kill at 67 and am getting 2% of lvl per 3 kills at 68
<br />

<br />
At lvl 67 they gave 9% aa per kill.
<br />

<br />
Check it out <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
